 discuss recent interesting measurements of the\neccentricities of the orbits of millisecond pulsars in low mass X-ray binaries.\nThe high values of the eccentricities found in some cases could be explained by\nassuming that the hadronic star, initially present in the binary system,\nconverts to a quark star due to the increase of its central density.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Sep 2015 17:27:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 19 Dec 2015 11:30:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-23"}
